item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::ApproximateNumberOfMessagesDelayed
item_prototype.description: The number of messages in the queue that are delayed and not available for reading immediately. This can happen when the queue is configured as a delay queue or when a message has been sent with a delay parameter.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::ApproximateNumberOfMessagesNotVisible
item_prototype.description: The number of messages that are in flight. Messages are considered in flight if they have been sent to a client but have not yet been deleted or have not yet reached the end of their visibility window.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible
item_prototype.description: The number of messages available for retrieval from the queue.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::NumberOfEmptyReceives
item_prototype.description: The number of ReceiveMessage API calls that did not return a message.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::NumberOfMessagesDeleted
item_prototype.description: The number of messages deleted from the queue.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::NumberOfMessagesReceived
item_prototype.description: The number of messages returned by calls to the ReceiveMessage API action.

item_prototype.name: SQS::{#DINAME}::NumberOfMessagesSent
item_prototype.description: The number of messages added to a queue.

trigger_prototype.name: SQS::{#DQNAME}::high number of messages in dead letter queue (LV={ITEM.VALUE})

trigger_prototype.expression: {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].last(0)}>0 and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].last(0)}<{$SQS_DLQ_MSG_VISIBLE_TH} and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].last(0)}>{Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].max(10m,10m)}
trigger_prototype.name: SQS::{#DQNAME}::messages in dead letter queue increased (LV={ITEM.VALUE})
trigger_prototype.description: This trigger is fired when the queue size increased

trigger_prototype.expression: {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].max({$PERIOD})}>{$SQS_DLQ_MSG_VISIBLE_MIN} and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].max({$PERIOD})}<{$SQS_DLQ_MSG_VISIBLE_TH} and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].max({$PERIOD})}={Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#DQNAME}"].max({$PERIOD},{$PERIOD})}
trigger_prototype.name: SQS::{#DQNAME}::messages in dead letter queue might not be reprocessed (LV={ITEM.VALUE})
trigger_prototype.description: This trigger is fired when the max queue size has no change within a period.

trigger_prototype.expression: {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#MQNAME}"].delta(1h)}>{$SQS_MASS_INCREASE_TH_LOW} and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#MQNAME}"].delta(1h)}<{$SQS_MASS_INCREASE_TH_HIGH} and {Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#MQNAME}"].last()}>{Template AWS SQS:SQS.ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible.Average["{$AWS_ACCOUNT}","{$AWS_REGION}","{#MQNAME}"].avg(1h,10m)}
